Like most assessment tools, the basic steps in CCHAAs include framing the assessment, assessing indicators, and monitoring and evaluation. The World Health Organization (WHO) guidance document on CCHVAAs describes these as [
 55]:
 
  
   Step 1:

Scanning and scope the assessment;
  
  
   Step 2:

Assess vulnerabilities;
  
  
   Step 3:

Assess future climate impacts;
  
  
   Step 4:

Assess adaptation opportunities;
  
  
   Step 5:

Manage and monitor risks through an iterative process, including an evaluation of health harms in other sectors.
